<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 16 at 12:33PM EDT  by NWS State College</headline>
<description>...A STRONG THUNDERSTORM WILL IMPACT CENTRAL HUNTINGDON AND
SOUTHWESTERN MIFFLIN COUNTIES THROUGH 100 PM EDT...
At 1232 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Huntingdon, moving east at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation
possible.
This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of central Huntingdon
and southwestern Mifflin Counties, including the following
locations... Mapleton, Mill Creek, Kistler, Newton Hamilton and
Shirleysburg.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...55 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
